CAPE TOWN - Cape Town City officials have found a large number of baby sharks on Strandfontein beach. Their heads, dorsal fins and tails were severed. READ: Still no sign of Great white sharks at False Bay The SPCA says shark fins are highly prized by poachers and fetch high prices, they are are also seen as a delicacy in some countries. Cape Town City Law Enforcement spokesperson, Wayne Dyason said the SPCA discovered the fish at about 09:00 on Saturday and were identified a deep water shark species.